GAURAV GUPTAGAURAV GUPTA (He/Him) 1st (He/Him) 1st - (.) | Kiet Group Of Institutions || - @IEEE Bombay Section | | DSA-C++ || Exploring Data Analytics - (.) | Kiet Group Of Institutions || - @IEEE Bombay Section | | DSA-C++ || Exploring Data Analytics
1w 1w
Summer Internships are just around the corner. It's high time that you start searching for one if you haven't any.

Since the number of candidates willing to intern at this time is at its peak, it gets hard to receive any decent offer if you delay your applications any further.

So let's talk about some of the credible sources that you can utilise to find quality internships that with real-world impact in them.

1) Government of India Internships -

The most interesting thing in a resume is when a person is interned in a national-level organization .

Not only do these internships deals with national-level impact but also reflect wonderfully well on your profile.

NITI Aayog, Ministry of External Affairs, DPIIT, Invest India, and Centre for Public Policy Research are some of the organisations that provide such internship opportunities.

2) Academic Internships

These are readily available for master's students, but a lot of undergraduate students pursue them as well.

For this, you will have to constantly keep an eye out for official internship schemes by different colleges including IIT, ISB and IIMs.

Moreover, you can reach out to the professors via cold mail at any time of the year to secure a massive level of research exposure in your area of interest.

3) College's Placement Cell -

Yes, I agree that most of the opportunities that come from here may not suit your interest and aspirations. But, completely ignoring this area can cost you that one good internship that could've been all that you were ever searching for.

Once or twice a month, you'll see opportunities for profiles such as Business Analyst, Data Analyst, Market Research or Consulting Intern that align with the goals of most undergraduate students.

It's one of the quickest methods to secure an internship and sort your summer. So, do not ignore it.

What is your experience of applying for summer internships? Is it too taxing? Or do you hear back from the recruiters readily?

#summerinternship #internship #consulting #placements #opportunities #marketresearch #experience #research #intern #business #skills# #recruiters #internships #resume #placement #placement2023 #placement2024

Our most direct path happiness can be found when we freely give our joy to others. Agree?

Here are 5 #reasons to give without #expecting anything in return:

1. When we give without expecting anything in return, blessings have a way of finding their way back to us. It allows us to help others just for the sake of helping, without any ulterior motive or desire for recognition.

2. #Giving without expecting recognition helps to cultivate a sense of humility, as we are not seeking validation for our actions.

3. We can feel good knowing that we were able to make a difference in someone else's life, even if nobody else knows about it.

4. Giving anonymously or without seeking recognition can also inspire others to do the same, creating a ripple effect of kindness and generosity.

5. Finally, giving without expecting recognition shows that we are motivated by a genuine desire to help others, not by a desire for personal gain or recognition. This can earn us respect and admiration from others over time, without having to seek it out.

Status is offline
Elizabeth HoughtonElizabeth Houghton 3rd+ 3rd+ Career Transition Coach | Job Search Mentor | Follow Your Path | Success on Your Terms | Stopping that Sunday dread | Finding Fulfilment | No Fluff ApproachCareer Transition Coach | Job Search Mentor | Follow Your Path | Success on Your Terms | Stopping that Sunday dread | Finding Fulfilment | No Fluff Approach
1w 1w
#AD Searching for a job can sometimes feel tough - youll be spending time and energy trying to send the best applications for the jobs which are best suited for you. However, an increasing amount of scammers are weaselling their way into our job searches.

Unfortunately, theyre getting better at targeting job seekers. This is something LinkedIn is taking action to combat.

:
Trusted employers never need paying as a part of your job search journey. So if someone asks you to pay for something or wants you to share sensitive personal or financial information before youve started the job.
If a job posting claims to give high pay for little work.
If youre asked to download encrypted software for an interview.
If you receive a job offer after one quick, remote interview that's another red flag.

If something doesnt seem or feel right or it seems too good to be true, then theres the possibility it is a scam. You can report this to LinkedIn by clicking on the three dots at the top right-hand corner of the job listing, then clicking report and simply selecting the reason.

I hope these tips help you feel better prepared to take on your job search more safely. Let me know in the comments below.

.

With the goal of providing more benefits for local communities and a better #transportation network, the Victorian Government's Level Crossing Removal Project is an initiative to remove all dangerous and congested level crossings (intersections where a highway crosses a railroad at-grade).

Melbournes level crossing removal initiative involved the removal of 20 level crossings and the #construction of 13 new stations along the Frankston Line by 2029. Faced with several construction planning challenges when working in congested areas among a large stakeholder group, the project team upgraded its digital approach to a more seamless integrated solution to ensure efficient design and timely delivery of the project.

ACCIONA used #SYNCHRO, along with other Bentley solutions, to reduce staging time by 67%. The project provided a digital asset that can now unlock new opportunities for the realization of an intelligent digital Victoria and was a winner at Bentley's 2022 Going Digital Awards in Infrastructure.

Do you often find yourself struggling to keep up with meetings? 
Do you wish to be more organized and productive in your meetings?
Follow these .

" " -

. :
It is crucial to come prepared and organized for meetings. Take the time to review the agenda, gather necessary information, and make a list of questions to ask. This way, you can plan and clear all your doubts before work.

. :
Have the agenda and the issues to be covered during the meeting close at hand to avoid wasting time. Keep a notebook, sticky notes, or an electronic device nearby to jot down important points discussed during the meeting.

. :
Provide clarity by discussing every point thoroughly with your team. Make sure everyone understands their roles and responsibilities and is aware of the meeting's objectives.

Are you ready to nail your next meeting? Implement these tips and see the difference for yourself.
